? What is NAT ( Network Address Translation ) technique / method but the router 
- Method used by Router uses to let multiple (private local address) devices on home network share one public ip address - Used across the internet 
- Translates Private IP Addresses to one single Public address 
- Faciliates communication between internal network and the internet 


? How does NAT work 
- Internal devices use public IP addresses 
- Router translates private IP to public IP 
- Faciliates communication with external networks 

Internal devices -> router ( changes private to public ) -> external networks 
Internal devices <- router ( changes public to private ) <- external networks 

-> ( this is a request ) 

? Types of NAT - 
- Static NAT = one to one mapping of a private to public address ( webcam so can easily reach the same public IP ) 
- Dynamic NAT = internal private address devices share a pool of public IP Addresses and are assigned one when needed for a session by the router

- PAT ( port address translation ) = sharing one public IP address to a lot of private address devices on a network 
- Router Works by using different port numbers to assign which traffic belongs to each device 



? Benefits of NAT for devops 
= conservation of public IP Addresses as there are a limited number of ipv6 / ipv4 public ip addresses 
= enhance network security 
= simplifies network design 




